For this task, create a security group under default VPC with the following requirements:
Name of the security group is datacenter-sg.
The description must be Security group for Nautilus App Servers
Add the inbound rule of type HTTP, with port range of 80. Enter the source CIDR range of 0.0.0.0/0.
Add another inbound rule of type SSH, with port range of 22. Enter the source CIDR range of 0.0.0.0/0.

AWS Console Steps:
Go to EC2 > Security Groups > Create security group.
Name: datacenter-sg, Description: Security group for Nautilus App Servers, VPC: Default VPC.
Add inbound rules for HTTP (port 80, source 0.0.0.0/0) and SSH (port 22, source 0.0.0.0/0).
Click Create security group.

AWS CLI Steps:

1. Create the security group using:
aws ec2 create-security-group --group-name datacenter-sg --description "Security group for Nautilus App Servers" --vpc-id $(aws ec2 describe-vpcs --query "Vpcs[?IsDefault==\`true\`].VpcId" --output text)

2. Add inbound rule for HTTP:
aws ec2 authorize-security-group-ingress --group-name datacenter-sg --protocol tcp --port 80 --cidr 0.0.0.0/0

3. Add inbound rule for SSH:
aws ec2 authorize-security-group-ingress --group-name datacenter-sg --protocol tcp --port 22 --cidr 0.0.0.0/0

4. Verify the Security Group:
To verify that the security group was created and the rules have been applied, run:

aws ec2 describe-security-groups --group-names datacenter-sg

aws ec2 describe-security-groups --group-names datacenter-sg | jq -r '.SecurityGroups[0].GroupName'

datacenter-sg

